benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/block - Block an account

covered: Valid Payload: TC01 and TC02 cover successful creation with minimal and full data payloads
Authorization/Headers: TC08 and TC11 cover missing header and unauthorized access
Input Validation & Security: TC07 (invalid accountId), TC10 (malformed JSON), TC13 (SQL injection in accountId), TC14 (malicious payload)
Missing/Malformed Body: TC09 (missing request body) and TC10 (malformed JSON)
Edge Cases and Validation: TC15 (empty pluginProperty), TC16 (maximum field lengths), TC17 (minimum values), TC18 (ignore extra query parameters)
Existence/State Scenarios: TC05 (no prior blocking) and TC06 (account not found)
Regression/Backwards Compatibility: TC23 (duplicate BlockingState), TC24 (backwards compatibility with old clients)
Integration with Plugins: TC21 (pluginProperty triggers plugin interaction), TC22 (plugin service unavailable)
Performance/Load: TC19 (slow downstream), TC25 (high concurrency), TC26 (resource usage under load)
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling tests are missing
Caching behavior tests (ETag / Cache-Control headers) are missing
500 Internal Server Error scenario not explicitly tested (only 503 for DB unavailability)
Content-Type and header validation beyond missing header (e.g., invalid Content-Type)
Timeout handling beyond slow downstream (e.g., downstream timeouts)
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to validate throttling behavior
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching validation
Add a dedicated 500 Internal Server Error scenario test (server-side failure separate from DB unavailability)
Add tests for Content-Type/header validation and additional header edge cases
Extend timeout/tests for downstream services under various latency scenarios
Enhance plugin integration tests with more complex plugin interactions and failure modes
